# Test-Driven Development Workflow

## Requirement Documentation
- Document in README.md under appropriate sections
- List test scenarios
- Define test data
- Specify coverage expectations

## Development Process
1. Write failing tests
   - Create test file
   - Write test cases
   - Verify tests fail

2. Implement minimal code
   - Add basic functionality
   - Add error handling
   - Verify tests pass

3. Refactor
   - Improve code quality
   - Maintain test coverage
   - Verify all tests pass

## Test Structure
- Use table-driven tests
- Name test cases descriptively
- Cover:
  - Happy paths
  - Error cases
  - Edge cases
  - Invalid inputs
  - Boundary conditions

## Continuous Testing
- Run tests between steps
- Verify coverage
- Check for race conditions
- Validate error handling
- Ensure cleanup
